<br>
unfortunately i know too little about him besides what ive seen on Alla's<br>
<br>
can anyone link a good, current strategy or answer these questions?<br>
<br>
is he slowable?<br>
is there a place to dodge the AE he shoots off? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elharinalokhem>Elharina Lokhem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 325<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 10:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> pretty sure he's not slowable anymore, used to be but after shaman slow got disease counters (so sont couldn't dispel it) they changed him. As for hiding from the ae, not really only way is to stay out of range until you are ready to do damage, WW being an outdoor zone means all that lovely terrain won't hide you for jack from his ae. <br>
Anyther thing if I remember right one of sonts ae's is a proc, often ended up wiping raids when the evil duck dragon enraged and he procced like mad, worth warning anyone in front of him that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113259" target="top">Sage Elharina Lokhem</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hibashira>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 10:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> If you are within LoS, his AE will hit you.  Heck, his AE hits even if you hide around the corners, any corners.  Resist don't help much, his AE lands even if you are at 300.  You really need a good MT to hold aggro so the first healer won't splat.  If your raid survive the first few heals, then its just DPS. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=retrievil>Retrievil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 11:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> Can't use geography/walls to hide from AEs outside.<br>
<br>
Sont is slowable, however he procs a dispell on himself (see below) every few seconds usually so its pretty much a waste of mana.  I suppose it might be worth it if you get lucky and he doesnt proc for 5 secs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2830&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
He also has a couple AE dispell procs, and a nasty DD one.<br>
<br>
 Sont is a kill him before he kills you fight basically.  We had a bit of a time learning him.  We kill him every time now by just going max offensive as soon as MT has a bit of aggro.  All melee offensive discs, casters (including shamans and druids) nuke.  His procs are totally random too so if he procs that DD on the MT 5 times in a row you might lose even if its all perfectly done otherwise. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/jpew/sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izelin>Izelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 11:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> Zerg!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veladorn>Veladorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>I have needs too!</span><br>  Posts: 1320<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 12:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> Sont is an unpredictable zerg fight, there is no strategy other then to do your best to stay behind him, have a right click buff and rush him.<br>
<br>
Oh, and he hates clerics.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Valas Defai</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;">A member of Insidious Blood</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211027&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:xx-small;">My Magelo</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1755<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 12:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> Sontalak basically is like a nonscript PoP encounter, hits very fast, has low HP comparable, and is absolutly shitty itemized for a) being non-script b) being trivial to access. <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
Arcanist<br>
Venril Sathir</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delaregarwiz>DelaregarWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 610<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 2:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> he has a seperate frontal ae that dispells like 4 buffs + some dmg, don't remember how much though <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89629" target="top"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Delaregar Stormtamer<br>
62 wizard</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273003" target="top"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Selt<br>
51 monk</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://stormwindguild.net" target="top">Stormwind</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://xevserver.com">Xev</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heofmanyfals>HeOfManyFals</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 476<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 3:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /sigh</span><hr size=1> You don't have to zerg him, you just need to kill him realtively quickly.<br>
<br>
Junk buff, MT with good taunt, healers spam heal until he is set into position.<br>
<br>
Watch pets, they can really screw up position for you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nukes are the name of the game.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hannduvdeth>Hannduvdeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 3:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with sontalak strategy</span><hr size=1> There is no such thing as a frontal AE.  It's either targetted or point blank.  The one you are referring to is targetted and has a relatively small AE range, therefore being behind Sont usually puts you far enough away from it.   His other AE, Molten Breath, is also targetted but has a huge range, so you are almost guaranteed to get hit by it.  One clicky item can keep your buffs on against that one.<br>
<br>
You need to be in melee range to land any resistable spells.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=26693.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=26693.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=26693.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=26693.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26693.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26693.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General EQ Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilation